        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="60" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d60">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710 Consultation (3A)/10–446</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        President of the Emergency Advisory Committee for Political Defense</hi>
                        (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Guani</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-10-31">October 31,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge your
                    Excellency’s communication of October 4, 1946,<note n="17" xml:id="d60fn17">Not
                        printed.</note> concerning the need to prevent dangerous Axis elements from
                    entering the Western Hemispheres especially from neutral countries, together
                    with the attached preliminary list of such persons heretofore in Spanish
                    territory.</p>
                <p>The Government of the United States welcomes the initiative taken by the
                    Emergency Advisory Committee for Political Defense concerning this subject, and
                    will be entirely disposed to cooperate in preventive action, in concert with the
                    other American Republics, along the lines of the recommendations made by the
                    Committee.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James</hi> F. <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
